[#category-theory]
=== Category Theory Perspective

In the category of sets (**Set**):

[stem]
++++
\begin{aligned}
& \text{Let } 1 = \{\ast\} \text{ (terminal object)} \\
& \text{Coproduct: } 1 \sqcup 1 \cong 2 \\
& \text{Where } 2 = \{\ast_1, \ast_2\} \\
& \text{Thus } |1 \sqcup 1| = |2| = 2
\end{aligned}
++++

[#complex-analysis]
=== Complex Analysis Extension

[stem]
++++
\begin{aligned}
& \text{Consider } z_1 = 1 + 0i, z_2 = 1 + 0i \in \mathbb{C} \\
& z_1 + z_2 = (1 + 1) + (0 + 0)i = 2 + 0i \\
& |z_1 + z_2| = \sqrt{2^2 + 0^2} = 2
\end{aligned}
++++

[#conclusion]
== Final Theorem and Conclusion

[.math-theorem]
=== Fundamental Addition Theorem (Peano Arithmetic)
[stem]
++++
\begin{aligned}
& \text{Using Peano axioms:} \\
& S(0) = 1 \\
& S(1) = S(S(0)) = 2 \\
& 1 + 1 = S(0) + S(0) = S(S(0) + 0) = S(S(0)) = 2 \\
& \square
\end{aligned}
++++

